## Persona Template Sections

### Characteristics

Add characteristics that matter: required skills or certifications, work environment details, tool proficiency. While some personas may be subdivided into archetypes by age, gender, or other segments, carefully assess the relevance of this level of detail. Not every dimension matters for every domain.
### Day in the Life

If the [[Value Stream Network]] has been developed for the domain - particularly built out to detail the business capability instances where the roles have been defined - use this to inform the daily flow. For customer segments navigating an organization's value stream and/or value stream network, draw upon or create a supporting [[User Journey Maps|journey map]]. Adding a visualization of the key points within the day can be valuable.

_Think of this as the persona's mission briefing - what does their typical day look like from touchdown to extraction?_
### Persona Goals and Objectives

This is the key section for understanding the motivation for a particular persona within a business domain. Link to the [[Business Architecture Motivation Measures|business measures]] whenever possible for coherency and relevancy within the domain architecture. If you're modeling in ArchiMate, map these to value, goal, or objective elements.

- **Experience Goals** - What do people want or not want within their day in the life within that domain? What makes their work easier versus more frustrating?
- **Organizational Goals** - How does this persona support achieving any of the measures for the domain or organization's objectives? What metrics move when they're successful?
- **Life Goals** - How does the role within that domain support that person's life goals? This may be particularly true for apprentice or entry-level positions where career trajectory matters.
### Persona Image

Skip real photos - use AI-generated images or illustrations. This signals that your persona is an archetype, not an actual employee. Plus, it avoids awkward conversations when someone recognizes themselves (or thinks they do). With the advance of artificial intelligence, creating images based on text descriptions is easier than ever.
## Persona Quality Checklist

Before you call your persona complete, validate against these criteria:

- [ ]  Fits on one page (physical or single screen)
- [ ]  Based on real role data (not guesswork)
- [ ]  Goals link to measurable business outcomes
- [ ]  Day-in-life reflects actual workflows
- [ ]  Validated with someone who actually does this job
- [ ]  Useful for developers/analysts outside the domain
- [ ]  Uses AI-generated or illustrated image (not real photos)
- [ ]  Cross-referenced to relevant value streams and capabilities